Update changelog.

Clean up the normalization of values in indexes.

The index is now consistently storing normalized (lower case) values. At
the moment this also means no non-string values, but those didn't exist
anyways.

Here's the list of new rules:

1. Indexes now always contain normalized (lowercase) strings.
2. get() does a normalized index search
3. lookup() first does a normalized index search and then a normalized
   non-index search (and avoids searching the index values twice)

This required also touching the construction of the subdivisions as
that directly touches the internal index values, too.

This likely also means that previously the index searches didn't
actually do anything useful (sigh) and might be much faster now.
